lassroom Observation Scheme -- tAppendix 6: Learning Journal Framework -- tAppendix 7: Coding Scheme0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis book presents mixed-methods research into Chinese students' willingness to communicate (WTC) in an EFL classroom context. The interrelationships between WTC and motivation, communication confidence, learner beliefs and classroom environment are examined using structural equation modelling on data collected in a large-scale survey. These results are then complemented and expanded upon in a follow-up multiple case-study that identifies six themes which account for fluctuations of WTC over time and across situations. The qualitative and quantitative data provide the grounds for the proposition of an ecological model of WTC in the Chinese EFL university classroom, which reveals that WTC is socioculturally constructed as a function of the interaction of individual and environmental factors inside and beyond the classroom walls.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aClassroom managementzChina. 0aCommunication in foreign language educationzChina. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxChinese speakersxSocial aspectszChina. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxChinese speakers. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingzChina. 0aSecond language acquisition. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aChinese EFL classroom.  aChinese learners of English.  aEFL classroom.  aL2 motivation.  aSLA.  aSecond Language Acquisition.  aWTC.  aindividual differences.  alearner beliefs.  alearner characteristics.  alearner differences.  awillingness to communicate.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Package